1938;;Judge Hardy's Children;;American;;George B. Seitz;;Mickey Rooney, Lewis Stone, Fay Holden;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Judge_Hardy%27s_Children;;Judge Hardy (Lewis Stone) has been appointed chairman of a special committee in Washington, DC. The Judge's daughter Marian (Cecilia Parker) is intoxicated by Washington's social life, while son Andy (Mickey Rooney) falls for a pretty daughter of a French diplomat. Thus, the judge is obliged to juggle his committee duties with his efforts to keep his children from making fools of themselves.[2]